%N A393318 Final square visited by a knight moving on a square-spiral numbered board when starting from square n and always moving to the lowest available unvisited square.
%C A393318 There are 1518 distinct values, see A306291, the last one being a(17390) = 16851 beyond which the terms enter a repeating cycle of values as the knight starts further and further away from the origin.
%C A393318 See A316667 and A306291 for further details and images of the paths.
%H A393318 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A393318/b393318.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A393318 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A393318/a393318.png">Image of the first 50000 terms</a>.
%H A393318 N. J. A. Sloane and Brady Haran, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RGQe8waGJ4w">The Trapped Knight</a>, Numberphile video (2019).
%e A393318 a(1) = 2084. See A316667.
%e A393318 a(175) = 104. This is the smallest possible final square number. See A306291.
%e A393318 a(11509) = 23134. This is the largest possible final square number. See A306291.
%Y A393318 Cf. A306291, A316667, A307422, A393472.
%K A393318 nonn,walk
